<AbstractNarration>We propose to hold a one and a half day workshop in Ann Arbor during the month of May 2005&lt;br/&gt;(exact dates to be determined) to gather together key contributors to the field of active&lt;br/&gt;sensing and sensor management. We will discuss the state-of-the-art in active sensing&lt;br/&gt;research, the main mathematical approaches to design and performance approximation, the&lt;br/&gt;problems solved and the problems remaining. This workshop will be a launching point for a&lt;br/&gt;monograph on active sensor management written by the workshop participants.</AbstractNarration>
